In a bid to ensure quality and futuristic education to its future generation, India said it will implement its New Education Policy. Indian Prime Minister, Narendra Modi announced this in his address to mark the 74th anniversary of India’s Independence. Delineating the need to accelerate developments in science and technology, and futuristic, quality education for its youth, Modi said the policy allows for the development of a new quality education system that will transform future challenges into opportunities.
He said with the New Education Policy young Indians can choose subjects (at school) based on their interests and talents, alongside the opportunity to realize their potentials. It also promotes learning in local languages. “It will strengthen the culture of ‘inclusion’ ‘innovation’ and ‘institution’ in the sphere of education. Imparting knowledge in the mother tongue has been given emphasis in order to help young minds grow spontaneously. This will strengthen Indian languages as the unity of the country. Youth empowerment is essential for building a strong nation. The policy is a right step in this direction,” Modi stressed. He charged the youths to take pride in being citizens of India and commemorate with gratitude their independence fighters who sacrificed their lives for an independent India.